<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-75-0658 </DOCNO><TEXT>The ideal propulsion system for the manned journey from earth to Marsis one that combines high thrust generation with very high specific impulse;it is presently suggested that only fusion power can maximize both ofthese parameters to the point where the interplanetary journey in questioncan be made in several days rather than, as at present, several months.A vehicle accelerating at 1g half of the way to Mars, and then deceleratingat the same rate for the remainder of the journey, would require a fusionpower plant of 1-terawatt output, or three orders of magnitude greaterthan the 1-gigawatt output of the largest terrestrial fission powerplants.</TEXT></DOC>